<topic xml:id="task-example"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Re-encrypting the encrypted system</title><!-- can be changed via merge
in the assembly -->
    <!-- add author's e-mail -->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       The topic gives instructions on how to change the default passphrase.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <note>
    <title>The step is not needed if you deployed your system using &jeosfirstboot;</title>
    <para>
    &jeosfirstboot; asks for a new passphrase during the deployment phase. After you enter it, the
    system is re-encrypted automatically, thus no further action is needed.
    </para>
  </note>
  <para>
    &productname; encrypted images ar delivered with a default LUKS passphrase. To secure your
    system, make sure that you change it after the system is deployed. To do so, proceed as
    describe bellow. Make sure to perform the steps in the same shell session.
  </para>
  
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Import the needed function to your shell:
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.root;source /shr/share/fde/luks</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Identify the underlying LUKS device and define further used variables:
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.root;luks_name=$(expr "`df --output=source / | grep /dev/`" :
      ".*/\(.*\)")</screen>
      <para>
        and:
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.root;luks_dev=$(luks_get_underlying_device "$luks_name")</screen>
    </step>
    <step xml:id="creating-key-files">
      <para>
        Create a key file that stores the default passphrase '1234' and a key file with the new passphrase.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Change the recovery password:
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.root;cryptsetup luksChangeKey --key-file <replaceable>PATH_TO_DEFAULT</replaceable> --pbkdf pbkdf2 "${luks_dev}" <replaceable>PATH_TO_NEW</replaceable></screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Reencrypt the LUKS device:
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.root;cryptsetup reencrypt --key-file <replaceable>PATH_TO_NEW</replaceable> ${luks_dev}</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Create a new random key and seal it with TPM
      </para>
      <screen>&prompt.sudo;fdectl regenerate-key --passfile <replaceable>PATH_TO_NEW</replaceable></screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Remove both of the key files you created in <xref linkend="creating-key-files"
        xrefstyle="template:step 3"/>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>Update the <filename>grub.cfg</filename> file by running:</para>
      <screen>&prompt.sudo;transactional-update grub.cfg</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Reboot the system.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
